<subSubSection pageId="41" pageNumber="42" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="41.[151,1437,1410,1756]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,281,1410,1436]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Head with transverse carina or conical tubercle (
<figureCitation box="[876,967,1410,1436]" captionStart="FIGURES 31–38" captionStartId="58.[151,269,1935,1959]" captionTargetBox="[222,1364,194,1911]" captionTargetId="figure-57@58.[222,1365,194,1911]" captionTargetPageId="58" captionText="FIGURES 31–38. Dorsal views. 31. Pereiraidium almeidai, ♀; 32. Scatimus ovatus; 33. Scatrichus bicarinatus; 34. Silvinha unica; 35. Trichillidium quadridens; 36. Trichillidium brevisetosum; 37. Trichillum heydeni; 38. Trichillum pauliani." pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Fig. 32</figureCitation>
). Dorsum lacking setiferous punctures. Abdomen with intersternal sutures clearly visible. Trochanterofemoral pit of anterior leg rounded. Mesotibiae and metatibiae each with two transverse lateral carinae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
